GulfTalent.com
Executive Administrator
Charterhouse
Abu Dhabi, UAE
Posted on: 1 May 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
Our client is a globally diversified investment institution that is wholly owned by the government of Abu Dhabi. They currently require an experienced Executive Administrator to join an expanding Real Estate & Infrastructure Department.
The role will provide support to the Regional Chief Financial Officer and a team of several section heads. You will be responsible for the correct and timely execution of documents alongside the maintenance of accurate and orderly filling.
You will also maintain agreed databases on debt and company secretarial matters.
REQUIREMENTS
The successful candidate should have significant experience in the management of complex legal or financial documentation.
You should be meticulous, have database experience as well as an expert knowledge of Microsoft Office. It is imperative that you hold a University Degree or equivalent, are Western educated and have English as a first language.
You should also be hard working, flexible in your approach and possess excellent communication and interpersonal skills.
ABOUT THE COMPANY
During the last ten years, Charterhouse has been operating across Dubai, Abu Dhabi and the GCC Markets. In many ways, we were the recruiter who established and set the standards within the regional recruitment industry benchmarking and innovating the service levels associated to Search and Selection.
Charterhouse understands the dynamics attached to talent acquisition, relationship management and the required service levels within the regional industry. Our heritage is now our main strength as we continue to work within our core markets to deliver key account management and strong contingency recruitment practices to our clients and candidates.
